# Assets Directory

This directory contains sample assets (images, audio, video files) that are catalogued by the Outsmart platform.

## Structure

The assets are organized as follows:
- `images/` - Image files (.jpg, .png, .gif, etc.)
- `audio/` - Audio files (.mp3, .wav, .flac, etc.)
- `video/` - Video files (.mp4, .mov, .avi, etc.)

## Usage

Assets placed in this directory will be automatically discovered and catalogued by the Python scripts in the `data/catalogue/` directory.

The catalogue system will:
1. Scan this directory for supported file types
2. Extract metadata from each file
3. Generate AI descriptions using Ollama (if available)
4. Create a searchable catalogue in JSON format

## Supported Formats

### Images
- .jpg, .jpeg
- .png
- .gif
- .bmp
- .webp

### Audio
- .mp3
- .wav
- .flac
- .aac
- .ogg

### Video
- .mp4
- .mov
- .avi
- .mkv
- .webm

## Examples

To get started, add some sample files:

```
assets/
├── images/
│   ├── logo.png
│   └── banner.jpg
├── audio/
│   ├── notification.mp3
│   └── background-music.wav
└── video/
    └── intro.mp4
```

Run `npm run python:run refresh` from the `data/catalogue/` directory to generate the catalogue.
